I have enjoyed each episode of Elementary up to this past week. I was so happy to have an intelligent mystery drama that didn't contain blood. I am not able to watch CSI, Grey's Anatomy etc, all good shows, but they all have people bleeding, or blood spurting out. I know I am not the only person out there with these feelings, so I hope the writers and producers will continue the first class work that all the beginning episodes showed. The relationship between Sherlock and Watson has been well developed, tension and dynamic interaction that can grow in a number of paths. As a fan of Lucy Liu, I was particularly thrilled to see her in this role of female Watson. The power of observation that Sherlock has in so phenomenal, and he has flaws, but the flaw of vengeance and torture was very disturbing. I